26
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:56,643
Harold Garrett was seventy-one years old.
He had lived alone on the same Tennessee

27
00:01:56,643 --> 00:02:02,727
farm his father left him since 1971. One
hundred and sixty acres of stubborn land,

28
00:02:02,727 --> 00:02:08,660
old fencing, and work that never ended.
He was not rich, not polished, and never

29
00:02:08,660 --> 00:02:13,992
wasted words. But in three counties,
people knew two things about Harold

30
00:02:13,992 --> 00:02:20,000
Garrett. He always paid what he owed. And
he never forgot anything that mattered.

31
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:26,259
His truck was older than some of the men
working at the bank. His boots carried

32
00:02:26,259 --> 00:02:32,758
half the county's dirt. Once every year,
for fifty-three years, he had driven into

33
00:02:32,758 --> 00:02:38,776
town and paid forty dollars for safety
deposit locker number one hundred and

34
00:02:38,776 --> 00:02:45,115
seven at First Valley Bank. He had done
