99
00:07:49,404 --> 00:07:49,680
had.

100
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:55,903
This story had started long before Carter
Blake was born. In nineteen seventy-one,

101
00:07:55,903 --> 00:08:02,126
Harold's father, George Garrett, signed a
quiet agreement tied to the family land.

102
00:08:02,126 --> 00:08:08,195
Most men ignored the fine print. George
Garrett did not. Buried near the end was

103
00:08:08,195 --> 00:08:09,040
one clause.

104
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:14,889
"If the land was ever reviewed, acquired,
or used by a bank for growth or

105
00:08:14,889 --> 00:08:20,900
acquisition," the clause read, "the
grantor or the grantor's heirs shall be

106
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:24,880
owed seven percent of all future assessed
value.".

107
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:31,461
George had three sons. Harold was the
youngest. He was nineteen when his father

108
00:08:31,461 --> 00:08:38,211
handed him the key and said three things.
"Keep the key. Keep paying the fee. And

109
00:08:38,211 --> 00:08:45,046
