115
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:14,492
The years passed. Harold married, had a
son, became a widower. His wife died when

116
00:09:14,492 --> 00:09:20,793
David was young. David grew up quiet,
went to Nashville, became a mechanic.

117
00:09:20,793 --> 00:09:27,350
Harold stayed on the farm, planting corn,
fixing fences, wondering why he kept

118
00:09:27,350 --> 00:09:30,160
paying for a box he never opened.

119
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:35,059
Then four months ago, everything changed.
First Valley Bank was sold to new

120
00:09:35,059 --> 00:09:40,488
ownership out of state. New branding, new
computers, new policies, and a new branch

121
00:09:40,488 --> 00:09:45,189
manager who had made his career by
humiliating people who couldn't fight

122
00:09:45,189 --> 00:09:45,520
back.

123
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:50,714
Two weeks ago, the bank did a county-wide
