164
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:48,869
"I expected that," Harold replied. He
stood slowly and buttoned his jacket.

165
00:12:48,869 --> 00:12:53,920
"You have thirty days. After that, I file
in federal court.".

166
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:58,474
"Mr. Garrett, this bank is not paying
money over some old paper," Blake said

167
00:12:58,474 --> 00:12:58,960
sharply.

168
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:04,160
"Thirty days, Mr. Blake." Harold picked
up the envelope and walked away.

169
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:09,233
The two tellers near the counter watched
him leave. Neither said a word. They

170
00:13:09,233 --> 00:13:14,373
remembered how Carter Blake had laughed
in the vault, how Harold Garrett never

171
00:13:14,373 --> 00:13:14,640
had.

172
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:18,900
Blake called the legal department that
afternoon. They called back the next

173
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:19,360
