176
00:13:28,897 --> 00:13:29,520
Nashville.

177
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:34,636
The hearing was held in a courtroom with
wood-paneled walls, a faded flag in one

178
00:13:34,636 --> 00:13:39,882
corner, and the kind of silence that made
every movement sound louder than it was.

179
00:13:39,882 --> 00:13:45,063
Carter Blake arrived first with two young
lawyers, both carrying matching leather

180
00:13:45,063 --> 00:13:50,244
folders and smooth voices. They spoke in
low voices and avoided looking at Harold

181
00:13:50,244 --> 00:13:51,280
when he entered.

182
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:56,986
Harold walked alone. No hurry, no
expression. He took his seat beside Frank

183
00:13:56,986 --> 00:14:03,309
Solis, the sixty-year-old property lawyer
who had spent three decades winning cases

184
00:14:03,309 --> 00:14:09,093
and no interest in dramatic speeches.
Judge Margaret Chan entered exactly on

185
00:14:09,093 --> 00:14:12,640
time. She had read every page the night
